<h4 id="1-problem">1. Problem</h4>

<h4 id="2-model-architecture">2. Model Architecture</h4>
<p><img src="/images/ai-dynamic-model-hmm-introduction.png" height="" width="" /></p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Discrete Transition Probability
\(p\left(q_{t} \mid q_{1}, \ldots, q_{t-1}, y_{1}, \ldots,
y_{t-1}\right)=p\left(q_{t} \mid q_{t-1}\right)\)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Measurer 
\(p\left(y_{t} \mid q_{1}, \ldots, q_{t-1}, q_{t}, y_{1}, \ldots,
y_{t-1}\right)=p\left(y_{t} \mid q_{t}\right)\)</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h4 id="3-model-parameters">3. Model Parameters</h4>
<ol>
  <li>$ \lambda={A, B, \pi} $
    <ul>
      <li>$\pi$ is the probability of the initial state</li>
      <li>A is the state transition matrix</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Major operations
    <ul>
      <li>
        <table>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Evaluate $p(Y</td>
              <td>\lambda)$: it needs the backward and forward algorithm</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </li>
      <li>$ \lambda_{\mathrm{MLE}}=\underset{\lambda}{\arg \max } p(Y \mid \lambda) $,
it needs EM algorithm</li>
      <li>$ \underset{Q}{\arg \max } p(Y \mid Q, \lambda) $</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

